description.narrative: Strengthen education sector legislative and policy frameworks, planning, coordination and budgeting, including for early learning, which contributes to Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, children and adolescents are protected from violence and HIV, learning and equipped with the skills to become active citizens.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported key milestones to strengthen child protection systems in Eswatini including development of National Gender Based Violence (GBV);and;Violence against Children (VAC) Coordination Mechanisms; finalization of Eswatini Alternative Care Guidelines; and development of a National Plan of Action and Monitoring and Evaluation Framework for Children (2022-2026). A digital Child Protection Information Management System was piloted to improve child protection data management. 11,924 women, men, and children (5,780) received physical and remote, UNICEF-supported GBV and VAC response services, and 14,746 women, men, and children (4,486) were reached with GBV and VAC prevention interventions.;375 service providers trained on VAC and GBV. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
